<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-text">
    <p class="eyebrow">Admin console</p>
    <h1>Welcome back, <%= current_admin&.english_name || current_admin&.email %></h1>
    <p>
      This placeholder mirrors the structure of the production admin. Replace these cards with the
      real KPIs, resource tables, and workflows your client needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <header>
    <h2>Starter metrics</h2>
    <p>Swap these for live KPIs once the backend endpoints are wired.</p>
  </header>
  <div class="metric-row">
    <% @metrics.each do |metric| %>
      <div class="metric">
        <span><%= metric[:label] %></span>
        <strong><%= metric[:value] %></strong>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <header>
    <h2>Next steps</h2>
    <p>Use this section to outline the backend work for your client engagement.</p>
  </header>
  <ul class="idea-list">
    <li><%= link_to "Fill out the temple profile →", admin_temple_profile_path, class: "link" %></li>
    <li>Connect real-world data sources to the KPIs above.</li>
    <li>Replace this placeholder with the first CRUD workflow (users, orders, bookings, etc.).</li>
    <li>Document the admin scope inside `docs/` for each new client.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
